{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/testLogSetFatalHandler(logFunc:userData:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/testlogsetfatalhandler(logfunc:userdata:)"]}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Installs a non-error fatal log handler which can be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"used to decide whether log messages which are counted","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"as fatal abort the program.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"testLogSetFatalHandler","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"logFunc","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GTestLogFatalFunc","text":"GTestLogFatalFunc"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"userData"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gpointer"},{"text":"? = nil)","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The use case here is that you are running a test case","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that depends on particular libraries or circumstances","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and cannot prevent certain known critical or warning"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"messages. So you install a handler that compares the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"domain and message to precisely not abort in such a case."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that the handler is reset at the beginning of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","